{
  "$comment": [
    "Tier-2 DB-state fixture spec for the `characters` SLIM ROW (Phase-2, main DB,",
    "the store-backed capstone sub-unit 2). One committed file drives BOTH sides:",
    "  - the v4 oracle (build-characters-slim-fixture.ts + characters-slim.ts) and",
    "  - the Rust port (quilltap-harness characters_slim tier-2 test).",
    "",
    "WHAT IT PORTS: the base-repository SQL CRUD (_create/_update/_delete) of v4's",
    "CharactersRepository over the `characters` table. v4's public create/update",
    "orchestrate the character vault; here we drive the protected slim-row internals",
    "directly via a thin subclass (the wardrobe-repo precedent) so the differential",
    "checks the actual slim-row marshaling. v4's overridden _create/_update strip the",
    "MANAGED_FIELDS (identity/description/manifesto/personality/exampleDialogues/",
    "pronouns/aliases/title/firstMessage/talkativeness/physicalDescription/",
    "systemPrompts/scenarios) before the write — those live in the vault now — so the",
    "persisted row is the non-managed complement. A fresh fixture's table still has",
    "the managed columns (ensureCollection generates them from CharacterSchema); both",
    "sides omit them from every write, so they sit at their DDL defaults identically.",
    "",
    "MARSHALING BANKED: seven nullable boolean columns (defaultAgentModeEnabled,",
    "defaultHelpToolsEnabled, canDressThemselves, canCreateOutfits, systemTransparency,",
    "coreWhisperEnabled, canBeCarina — present 0/1 AND absent NULL); two boolean-",
    "default columns (isFavorite, npc); a typed JSON-object column",
    "(defaultTimestampConfig — all nine keys present in schema order, AND null); an",
    "open JSON column (sillyTavernData — null AND single-key, the multi-key seam kept",
    "out); two typed-struct array columns (partnerLinks {partnerId,isDefault},",
    "avatarOverrides {chatId,imageId} — empty AND non-empty); a string-array column",
    "(tags); an enum TEXT column (controlledBy llm/user); many nullable UUID columns.",
    "",
    "HARNESS FORM: pinned zero-normalization. The slim CRUD honors pinned",
    "id/createdAt/updatedAt (CreateOptions on create; explicit updatedAt on update),",
    "so the persisted rows match v4 byte-for-byte with NO normalization.",
    "",
    "SAFETY: testPepperBase64 is a THROWAWAY 32-byte key (the same one folders/tags/",
    "wardrobe use). NOT the real Friday pepper; safe to commit."
  ],
